les. Altogether, these essays suggest that Singapore had a pre-1819 past that was deeply connected to the millennium-long maritime history of the Straits of Melaka and its links to the South China Sea and the Indian Ocean.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Aug 2021) 4aAsian History. 7aHISTORY / Asia / Southeast Asia.2bisacsh1 aAcri, Andrea, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAndaya, Leonard Y., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBorschberg, Peter, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aChong Guan, Kwa, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aChong, Terence, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFlecker, Michael, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHeng, Derek, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMiksic, John N., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSinclair, Iain, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aYew Seng, Tai, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus PP Package 2021 Part 2z978311074335740uhttps://doi.org/10.1355/978981495142540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9789814951425423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9789814951425.jpg  a978-3-11-074335-7  DG Plus PP Package 2021 Part 2b2021  aEBA_CL_HICS  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_HICS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK